  <br> 
  <br>
  <strong>Linear equation</strong> is an equation in which the highest power of variables is 1 e.g. y = 5x – 3. The <strong>x</strong> and <strong>y</strong> are variables, <strong>5</strong> is the coefficient of <strong>x</strong> and <strong>3</strong> is the constant in the equation.
  <br>
  <br>
  Linear equation or equation of a straight line is an equation such as; y = mx + c where m and c are constants <strong>or</strong> ax + by + c = 0 (e.g. 2x – y – 3); where a and b are coefficients and c is a constant
  <br>
  <br>
  <strong>Variables</strong> are regarded as store of values i.e. symbols representing the numbers we do not know yet or letters standing for the unknown(s) in algebra. Variables can be <strong>independent</strong> and <strong>dependent;</strong>
  <br>
  <br>
  <strong>Independent variable</strong> is a variable that can stand on its own and its value does not depend on another variable(s).
  <br>
  <strong>Dependent variable</strong> is a variable whose value depends on another variable(s).
  <br>
  <br>
